## §5 Routing & role guards

**Routing library**: {{ROUTING_PATTERN}}

<!-- React Router v6 / Next.js app router / TanStack Router / etc. -->

**Role-gating pattern**: {{ROLE_GUARD_PATTERN}}

<!-- e.g.:
- `useRoles()` hook at src/hooks/useRoles.ts returns typed booleans (isPublisher, isAdmin, ...)
- ProtectedRoute component wraps gated routes
- Inline role string comparisons (flag as anti-pattern)
-->

**Rules:**
- {{ROUTING_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Gated pages are wrapped by the repo's ProtectedRoute or role-guard HOC; never redirect-on-mount inside the page component.
- New routes added to the central router file with `lazy()` imports.
- No route-based detail views for a record that opens as a Dialog elsewhere — see the repo's DESIGN_SYSTEM.md §3.3.
-->

**Reference files:**
{{ROUTING_REFERENCES}}

