## §6 State management

**Pattern**: {{STATE_PATTERN}}

<!-- e.g.:
- React Query for server state
- React Context for auth / language / theme (list the contexts)
- localStorage tokens only; user state is in-memory
- Zustand / Jotai / Redux (if used)
-->

**Rules:**
- {{STATE_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- User profile, roles, tokens live in AuthContext. Do not read `localStorage.getItem('user')` outside AuthContext.
- Feature-local state stays in feature hooks / components. Don't add a new global context without a cross-cutting reason.
-->

